,Recommended,244160,33021002,Posted: 29 June,all,HellJester616,"Homeworld remastered collectionHomeworld is one of my favorite games, when i heard it was coming to steam, i immediately bought it (and it was the reason i got into steam) and when i got my first game, i couldn't be more excited.By playing both remastered and classic versions, i can see all the improvements they have done, and unlike many remasters out there in popular games, this one actually improves some gameplay mechanics rather than just giving some crispy new graphics.Classic versionHomeworld classic can be described as a gorgeous game, the universe backgrounds always give a sensation of awe and even an insight on how small we are in the universe. The gameplay is definitely a new turn on RTS games, where adding the element of 3d makes it more interesting (yet not frustrating) where most RTS games tend to be on one plane.The movement is simple, selecting ships (by changing the focus of the camera) definitely makes it better to select groups of ships, movement and even strategy towards surprising your enemy.The difficulty can be challenging yet by replaying levels you learn how to advance better. Some levels are hard, some are easy, and by recollecting al resources, you can build a strong fleet.The game is fairly long and it can take a while to complete from beginning to end. With 16 levels, every single level provides a new challenge and different objectives that bring a small variety to the game.Multiplayer is where i spend most of the time, the wide variety of maps and different forms of gameplay can abroslf oneself in, where survival and strategy (and even trying different AI's) can be very interesting.ProsInteresting story and immersive gameplayGorgeous graphicsGreat multiplayer and very strategy reliantConsShips run out of fuel easily, this can make docking often fail the levelLoading and unloading ships from the mothership takes forever!Homeworld remasteredThe remastered version brings new challenges and missions for the ones trying to reach hiigara once again, adding even better graphics and new gameplay mechanics not present on the classic version.The graphics are the first impression on the remastered version, shadows are better, textures are of higher quality, and the backgrounds by far are the best aspect of it. Being in awe of this graphical upgrade, these can be the best remasters i have ever seen.Gameplay adds new elements not present on the classic version, such as adding cost to researching new technologies and separating formations in 2 (or more) groups in case the ship group is too big. The UI gets a whole new redesign, such as seeing the gameplay as the same time as you build ships/research/manage launching ships instead of the previous version, which you had to enter another screen to do so. Now the UI adds which group ships are active and status of ships, such as defending, attacking, harvesting, etc.Harvester ships can now collect more rubble lying in space, which on the previous version they only harvested asteroids. Which also now in the remastered version, ships show their path trajectory, delimited by a line, these show where ships are supposed to go, these ""lines"" now even show which ships to attack, where will they dock, and where will the ship go to harvest.The difficulty seems to be toned up, where now ships take more shots to be destroyed and formations take more effect into how to destroy an enemy ship. One aspect that i didn't like is the lack of consistency in tactics, where in the classical version, one could see the difference between evasive and agressive, now here both seem to be the same and asking a ship to be defensive - evasive, they still seem to hold unto the same tactic.Multiplayer adds new elements of gameplay, for those even wanting to play with the new graphics in a classic multiplayer environment, options for ""classic multiplayer match"" can go on. Multiplayer even brings new races besides the Kushan and the Taiidan, the Vaygr and the Hiigarans where more variety comes into play.ProsAmazing new graphics and same immersive and awesome gameplayImproved UI better for controlling ships betterGreat multiplayer with both classic and remastered versionConsThe building system separated into classes, why change it when the classic version was fine? pressing alt+l brings a seamless versionThe system doesn't seem to remember about some choices, if i already pressed alt + l to see all building ships, why changes back to class building? same goes for resizing windows and ship information (tab)It's harder to find your own ships on the sensors manager, when you wanna bring up reinforcements, you don't know where to move, a con, yet not a big problem.Ships take forever to go from one point to another, specially capital class vessels (You'll see this in the last mission), where sometimes it took about 35 minutes to reach one point of the map. Fortunately, i wasn't in a rush.Even though the cons seem to be more detailed than the pros, the pros by far outweigh the cons, making this game have a few cons amongst many many pros.Turanic Raiders retreatAs an add-on, a mission previously cut from the original missions, and being brought back in the remastered version, we embark on an unseen adventure where our mission is to stop the Turanic raiders from reaching their homeworld. This mission was originally cut from the story due to the developers considering the mission too hard (Just like Super mario bros 2 returned in the lost levels) and also it was inconsistent for the fleet command to be chasing pirates instead of focusing on returning to their beloved planet.What can i say about this mission? We see a new background element present to our left, which is the Turanic homeworld, an element not present anywhere else in the game. With nice detail and sharp graphics, we get to even know a little bit more about these space pirates.The mission is very simple and straightforward, the Turanic raiders have emerged from hyperspace a few kilometers off their planet and we must destroy them before they reach safety on their planet. Armed with some frigates and scouts, we're quickly introduced towards 2 enemy carriers and many beam laser frigates (or however those enemy ships are called). When approached, the carriers will let out a swarm of fighters which slowed considerably my computer and will retaliate at any cost.The mission itself can be easy and destroying the 2 carriers will complete the objective, the enemy didn't managed to destroy any of my frigates and focusing full firepower towards the carriers will destroy them easily. However, i won't deny that the mission was fun, playing it for the first time and finishing it left me wanting more. Fortunately, there's Homeworld 2.ConclusionsHomeworld remastered collection brings a new twist on the game i loved back in 1999 and i love it now, both the remastered and classical versions are awesome games to buy and enjoy for hours. Where Hiigara needs to be claimed by its rightful owners.As for homeworld 2, i shall bring my thoughts into it as soon as possible.9.9/10 Amazing RTS game, and one of my best in my library."
