76561197986912394,Not Recommended,244160,32168710,Posted: 3 June,all,the_moidart,"As one who grew up playing the original Homeworld, I was severely disappointed by HW Remastered.Pros: Shiny.Cons: Too shiny, at times. The visuals are of course way better, but some maps have so much glare you can't see. On top of that, there's a massive reduction in functionality from the original game.To name a few: projectiles still use HW2's disappointing percentage to hit based system, instead of the original's wonderful yet fair physics system. Do you want to see a single fighter flying in a straight line not be hit by literally dozens of frigates? The dumbing down of physics, of ballistics, and of ship roles is in some ways even worse than Homeworld 2. In Homeworld 2, the system may have been a step backwards, but it was *balanced*. Homeworld Remastered is an extremely unhappy marriage of Homeworld 2's inferior gameplay engine with Homeworld 1's ship statistics.The campaign is poorly balanced to cover up the limitations of the new engine. Missile destroyers don't wipe out fighters anymore due to Hw2 engine's terrible missile physics? Add 30 assault frigates that can't hit them either! Capturing the frigates in mission 3 results in them being recycled instead of sent into your service? Send less enemy frigates! Salvage corvettes disable enemy ships before fully docking with them due to the hijack of Marine frigate code from Hw2? Popcap them low!Trust me people, stick with your original disks, copies, whatever. Don't pay for this minimum effort pallet swap. (Yes, the models are clearly copied from the free work of modders for Hw2). And don't buy it because it has the original game, that's just sad. Homeworld 1 deserved a new engine, that could deliver a more beautiful experience of the original masterpiece, not this 3/4 finished hackjob.And I'm told this is the 'fixed' version xD"
