76561197977698577,Recommended,244160,14664424,"Posted: 26 February, 2015",all,Ahmazzan,"Only just getting back into these great remasters, but without doubt the amount of effort expended here far surpasses most other ""HD remasters"".The Good:-The textures and cinematics have been updated and have improved in quality to a staggering degree,-The Audio, both music and dialogue, are excellent and crystal clear,-The gameplay is just as fun and immersive as I remember.-A plethora of new built-in skirmish features such as king of the hill style elements and of course the cross-race battles, all optional, and all great additions that keep the gameplay more current.-Also retains its predecessors' knack for displaying beautiful graphics with very light load on the system, even older computers should make it look very fancy indeed.Any downsides? Well:-One or two tech hiccups, in particular a CTD graphics bug which, for me at least, was solved by turning off shadows, not a huge sacrifice, especially in space, but a little annoying.-I have heard of other bugs, though have experienced none of them myself, but so far my game time is limited to the campaign and skirmish.-You also have to create a third-party account for multiplayer - painless and quick, but you have been warned.Conclusion? All in all 100% solid gold angel-moon cheese! A certain buy for any long term fan of the series, and VERY highly recommended for any fan of RTSs in general wanting a breath of old (but ironically, very fresh) air! Get it now!"
