,Recommended,244160,14660211,"Posted: 26 February, 2015",all,Shimmering Sword,"Having finished the included HW1 campaign so far I feel I can put in a good review of this remaster effort.First up getting it out of the way, we all know it but it must be said. The updated visuals are great! Not much more to be said there, the franchise has aged well visually, and now it looks even better.Sound is good, though in some zoomed in situations it can get buggy. I suspect docked fighters may be emitting engine sounds currently, causing quite a racket. Other than that I don't recall any issues.Gameplay is much improved with the HW2 style UI placed into the HW1 campaign. Sometimes the campaign difficulty can be brutal, but at least you won’t find yourself needlessly losing so many ships due to fighting against the interface and AI behavior.The addition of HW2 style end mission resource collection is also going to save you hours of work and fill your pockets between missions. Rather than having to seek out every pocket of resources on a map manually long after your objectives are complete, you can now simply hyperspace jump out and watch all remaining resources auto-deposit into your stores. This combined with smart battle management means you won’t be so dangerously broke all the time.Bugs I've observed in a 9 hour playthrough of the remastered HW1 campaign:-At least 3 times a keypress ('esc' did it one time) has caused my game space to go black. Fixed by saving, then re-loading that save.-Occasionally small objects will confuse AI navigation, either bumping into them, or treating them as large invisible walls. On the last level I had to fly high over a sparse asteroid belt that I don't recall being an obstacle in the original.- I had ONE full game crash that happened at random. not too bad for 9 hours of play on day one.I highly recommend this game to those looking to replay a classic, and those trying it for the first time. The campaigns will throw a lot of curve balls at you, and having to restart a mission, or even loading up from an earlier mission will be necessary at times, but at the core level I think this is an easy RTS to pick up, not to mention the great story."
