76561198030242426,Not Recommended,244160,14720872,"Posted: 1 March, 2015",all,Ike Jager,"(Disclaimer: This is for those who played and loved the very first Homeworld)Update; Now there is this ""General Failure"" crash plaguing the remastered that prevents mods and half the vanilla game. Did some digging and this crash has been happening for almost a year with no sign of a patch..... Still a buggy mess...I love the Homeworld series. It is beautiful in story and visuals, and fantastic gameplay and mechanics in the classics.(Homeworld 1 RM review)In short:I was fanboying over the visuals and sound and was having fun until I encounted more and more bugs and poor design decisions. I got too disappointed with the quality of the game as a whole to continue playing. It is Gearbox trying to mash Homeworld 1 into Homeworld 2's engine and failed, and feels rushed.In long:Homeworld RM is a HUGE upgrade in visuals and quality (stupid sexy Taiidan Heavy Cruiser)Sounds are cleaned up and sounds so much clearer and textures are great in HD (again Taidan Heavy Cruiser, I can't get over it!). UI was also updated and now a little bit more user friendly, no longer do you need to go to a WHOLE other screen for research, construction and hanger.However, it is not without its bugs, and there are lots of bugs and poor design decisions.Formations and Stances do not work as intended (I.E. Sphere formation do not surround targets, strike craft just break formations rendering formations useless. Stances do not give appropriate buffs like increased speed for evasive and increased fire power for aggressive.)Some units are unnecessarily changed (I.E repair units must now ""Dock"" with their targets to repair instead of repairing from a range.)Unit A.I. isn't all that good (I.E. strike craft tend to crash into asteroids and other objects in some missions)Units lifespan seems to be significantly shortened (I.E. A whole strike group of frigates won't last five minutes against a single heavy cruiser, same for strike strike craft to frigates. Rendering smaller ships hard to use or even worth using)Sound bugs (I.E. strike craft engines won't disappear if you hear them while docking)First experience with Homeworld with steam workshop mod support and sound just ceased to exist and gameplay was barely playable.And the most game breaking bug is RANDOM DESKTOP CRASHESit seems that Gearbox was trying to mash Homeworld 1 and 2 together when them both use very different mechanics and really messed up Homeworld 1 RM. Homeworld 1 IS NOT homeworld 2.I understand this is still new and update are incoming but for right now and my opinion is subject to change to updates. Until the game is more polished up and bugs ironed out, I just can't recommend this remaster in its current state. I still perfer to play the CD versions because it is much more stable. Even though this is just Homeworld 1 RM review, it is still half the package."
