76561197989894301,Recommended,244160,14656195,"Posted: 25 February, 2015",all,Warchild,"The homeworld Remasterd collection is without a doubt an amazing piece of work.All the controls are the same (if you can remember back that far, 15 years IS a long time).The graphics, which were amazing 15 years ago, are even better in this remastered version. Even the cut-scenes have been updated and even look better. Everything has been completely updated including the sounds.Some things were added to the game, such as fleet grouping controls.For example:Selecting 10 vessels and groupling them as fleet 1 then selecting 5 of those vessles and making them group 2, all vessels in the fleet remain group one as well as the 5 that are also group 2.This was something that wasn't included in the original Homeworld when it first came out...at least as far as I can remember...lol...it has been 15 years.Gearbox also updated the play screen with fleet info, mission recall data, and que update that was included in (the lost homeworld game) Cataclysm as well as Homeworld 2. So some helpful bits have been added to make the game what it should have been 15 years ago, but Gearbox hasn't altered the game away from what it was, which was awesome in its own state.Even the tutorials are still helpful in playing the game. Even if you've never heard of the game and decided to buy it, playing a tutorial in homeworld will definitely give you all the info needed for basic game play. This also trickles into Homeworld 2 as they have the same controls ;-).As far as I can tell, everything that was part of the original is included in the remastered version. Since I haven't played through completely, I can't tell if the original song The Ladder- by YES was included as the end song. Its a little over 9 minutes long I think LOL, so you can't miss it.All in all, the game remains one the THE BEST RTS games in the genre. Definitely a must have...especially since the original PC game has a very good chance of not working on the newer and faster PC's, not to mention with the updated graphics cards.I've only seen a handful of games that have been remastered, but only a couple of this age. Gearbox has definitely done a great job with The Homeworld Remastered Collection.Definitely buy this game."
