,Recommended,244160,14654314,"Posted: 25 February, 2015",all,Unhinged,"A few things that I have observed about Homeworld 1 remastered so far (Just finished mission 4)-No fuel system, making strike craft more useful for prolonged missions without support-Repairs of strike craft and Capital Ships seem to be free (Vanilla they were not)-Research now costs RU (In vanilla they were not)-Large enough ships now leave debris when destroyed (Turanic Carrier), which can now be salvaged for RU by Harvesters and Salvage Corvettes.-You can still capture ships, expect an all star-cast of Turanic, Taidaan and Kadeshi Capitals fighting for your cause (Just not the two Assault frigates from Mission 3, nor the Turanic Carrier)-Ships have problems staying in formation.-No seperate screen for research and ship building, meaning you have better situational awareness than you did in the Vanilla Game-I was hoping for a patrol control, but you only have a waypoint mode that cannot be used to create a permanent patrolThere may be more changes that I haven't noticed yet but those are the highlights. Can't wait till someone creates the inevitable Battlestar, Star Citizen, Star Trek, Star War, Babylon 5 mods for this game."
