,Recommended,244160,14695828,"Posted: 28 February, 2015",all,[VGN]Ravenheart,"The game that defined space RTS, remastered in glorious HD. I cannot express with words what this game evokes in me, pure joy and pleasure of once again guiding a people across a vast galaxy to defeat a foe that is far superior in every way.This is a game that any RTS and/or space junkie should play in his lifetime, not because it looks good and runs superb on practically any modern PC. But because the story and narrative of the game is so well written and executed that by the end of the game you feel connected to it, to the characters and to the ships you've commanded. The remastering done is simply put amazing, both the visual quality, sound fidelity and atmosphere is superb. Detailed ships, nebulas, asteroid belts and clusters of light all basked in the beautiful galactic background - SPACE.The mechanics of the original game are intact, all the clever ways to manipulate the outcome of battles is there. The balance of things has been brought in-line and the type of units matter. The mechanics are much clearer when it comes to unit types, don't expect a flurry of ion cannot frigates to easily defeat a destroyer or heavy cruiser, likewise assault frigates do big damage to slower moving corvettes and struggle with fast interceptors. The utility units are now really useful in big fights and a gravitywell generator and a cloak generator do wonders to turn the battle, especially if you are being bombarded by fighters and corvettes. Capital ships perform as they should, massive firepower and generally low speed, they will decimate every frigate and likewise because of their heavy armor are much harder to kill by frigates.As of this writing the game is at v1.2, the only problems that I've encountered are minor AI bugs. Specifically resource collectors will not automatically harvest resources if their nearest asteroid/cloud is out of range they just stop and you have to re-issue the harvest command. Ships sometimes fail to follow/guard another ship, they simple stop and you have to either re-issue the guard command or manually move them nearby. There have been a few slowdowns where the mouse and map freeze for a few secs, but those were no more than 5 in the whole campaign.Generally none of the above bugs affect the actual gameplay and you can be certain that they are not game breaking."
