76561198022263223,Recommended,244160,14659257,"Posted: 26 February, 2015",all,jeandeaux,"Day 1 review:This is a very good remastered version, I'm only 5 missions into the remastered HW1 and thus far it's pretty much as advertised, a remastered version of the original, though it's definately not the same mechanics.  The UI has been redone, and redone very well.  The original musical scores so far have remained and most of the voice actors are also the same, though the updated dialog seems a bit rushed on delivery and a ""small"" amount of that original emotion has been lost, but overall still very good, and if you've never played before you'll probably never notice but is something to enjoy in the classic version if you opt to play that.The graphics are fantastic and the new animations are quite impressive, love the new booms and kapows!  There are a few issues in the remastered version, formations aren't quite working right, support ships aren't supporting correctly, and you're not able to select your desired race in the campaign mode anymore.  So the old tactics need to altered to compensate for the new mechanics a bit, hopefully we'll see updates to correct these issues.Overall a very respectful and appreciated update to an old classic I actually still played from time to time."
