,Recommended,244160,16090527,"Posted: 30 May, 2015",all,Ventus,"What can I say about the greatest game ever? This game stands at the top of a list of extremely amazing game.- Story is top notch. Pick whatever term you want. Classic. Epic. Gripping. They all apply.- Gameplay was/is unrivaled. If side scroller would be 1 plane of movement. Other greats like Age of Empires and Command and Conquer would be 2 planes of movement, but Homeworld offers a true space RTS experience with 3 planes of movement. Swarm from the front, back, left, right, above him, under him, and everything in between. Limited resources per map mean that you need to manage your ships with some level of care (or get big on swarming enemy units with salvage corvettes).- Soundtrack is a cut above all others. Few experiences can top being hit with shocking revelations followed by insurmountable odds all to the timeless masterpiece of Samuel Barber's Adagio for Strings, vocal arrangement, Agnus Dei. More recent music-in-games titles that I would compare this level of excellent soundtrack to would be the Mass Effect Soundtracks and the Witcher 3 Soundtracks, as an example of 'Damn quality game music'.- Modding is somewhat alive. There are quite a few very solid mods for the game. Most notably the Star Wars mods, Mass Effect mods, Star Trek Mods, and all other SciFi reimaginings.- There was/is multilayer capability, but only in skirmish mode.I highly recommend this game for everyone. I wouldn't suggest that its multiplayer experience will grip your gaming attention for months or years, but the single player campaign here is something that can stick with you for a lifetime."
