,Recommended,244160,14658619,"Posted: 25 February, 2015",all,TheNut,"""The mothership has cleared the scaffold. We are away.""It's a time warp back into the past. One of my favorite RTS games makes a return with remastered enhancements that bring new life back to the Homeworld universe. Gearbox and Blackbird Interactive did a good job with the enhancement and I hope this success will continue to drive forward as they expand on the series. I haven't played any multiplayer yet as I'm focusing on the campaign and skirmishes. This is one of those games you want to bath in the full treatment and not rush any one particular feature. There's plenty to do and much value to absorb.Graphics+ Plenty of in-game options to enhance graphical quality.+ Models and textures are pretty sharp and detailed.+ Nice explosion effects.+ Lots of tiny details like ship damage decals, resource extraction effects, lens flares, sun rays, etc.+ Space environments are beautiful.- Shadows are a bit ""noisy"" around the edges. Not as high calibre like other games.- UI is a bit dated looking and could have been enhanced better.Audio+ Music suits the gameplay and the environments well. Quality is very crisp.+ Sound quality is pretty good and feels crisp as well.+ Explosions and cannons have a good punch on my sub.- Game lacks 3D positional audio, which would have enhanced the immersion as your camera rotates around ships and battles.Gameplay+ AI gives a good challenge. It keeps the pressure on as you foucs on survival.+ Good balance of combat & time investment. Skirmishes are not to long and not to short. You're always on the move.+ Classic RTS that sticks to the tried and true formula. Research, build, and tactics all within a space theme.- Little awkward there's no easy way to pan around quickly, or that the camera has a limit on the zoom-in/out range. In most modern RTS games, you move around quickly. Given the 3D positions in Homeworld, it can be awkward to get your camera in the right position without first orienting it on an object nearby, then moving over to where you want to go.Campaign / Single Player+ Just like the original, only better with the new HD visuals and audio.+ Challenging missions and interesting story with a sense of adventure.Quality+ Haven't run into any breaking issues so far.- ESC key doesn't bring up the menu like you would expect in most PC games.- PrintScreen is not the default screenshot key. ScrollLock is (like what?). Can't seem to bind it to PrintScreen either.Overall+ Would recommend this game. Homeworld is fun RTS, now with better visuals and audio. Combined with modding support, the possibilities are open for the community to introduce new scenery, new game modes, total conversions, etc. Add on 2 games + the originals, plenty of campaign missions, adventerous story, good music, AI skirmishes, and multiplayer. There's a lot of value here and if you haven't tried the Homeworld series before, consider checking this little gem out."
