,Recommended,244160,14661172,"Posted: 26 February, 2015",all,BoneDaddy,"Homeworld Remastered, is a good example of how a remaster should be.  This game consist of all the homeworld games to date (except for deserts of kharak).  If you're an RTS fan, this is a big must-have to any space fans and RTS fans out there.  Full 3D control, no constricted to the usual 2d plain that some space rts games have.  A long, challenging single player with lots of ways to finish them.  If you plan on playing the campaign, good luck, the difficulty in this game can go from easy to insane in a short time, mainly depends on how large your fleet is on later missions.Homeworld 1 Remake.  It has issues.  The biggest offended is the fact its just or feels more like a Homeworld 2 mod, but I guess its understandable, especially since they want all the races to be playable in skirmish or multiplayer, so they gotta keep them in the same engine.  The problem, a lot of HW1 features a missing.  So far they fixed some of them, mainly repair beams and I believe the harvesting.  All they need now is to brick back real time ballistics instead of an RNG chance system that homeworld 2 uses.  The other thing they need to fix is formations, luckily they're on the work for that, and the patch looks very promising.Homeworld 2 remake.  Since the remaster is using the HW2 engine, anyone who played the classic version already know how the gameplay is.  To the newcomers, homeworld 2 is the result when a developer is rushed to release a product, before release, the story was  to be much more larger (look up Homeworld 2: Dust Wars) however despite this, Homeworld 2 has one of the biggest or dedicated modding community out ther, check the workshop or the HW2 MODDB if you wanna see.The things Homeworld 2 improved upon is the gameplay and obviously graphics (look at the classic HW1 and HW2, the difference in graphics is big) and the remaster just makes HW2 (and 1) a lot more beautiful.Gameplay is good, its one of the best an RTS game offers, especially with its full 3D movement.  In a multiplayer match, you can send your units downwards (or upwards) towards the opposing fleet, and they'll never know whats coming to them (especially since we're so used to the usual 2D plain in RTS games)  The story is simple in the game yet emotional, especially since the Race you play as is almost extinct (spoilers)  Multiplayer is great too, even if you go against AI, its still a blast, because of the gameplay, you may find yourself too distracted looking at whatever your units are doing.tl;dr  Its a Must-have RTS game, buy it.+Great gameplay+Great soundtrack+Beautiful graphics+great sounds+good lengthy campaign+great modding community-HW1 features are missing-not a lot playing online (though it depends where you live and if you have good connection)-HW1 Remake feels more like a HW2 mod"
