rt. In the original, all ships that could be built were listed on ONE screen, and the text was small enough that you didn't need to scroll. Units under production were displayed over the text, simple and as wholesome as apple pie. In this version you have to click on the category of ship you want to build first, and then select the ship class to build. You cant miss it because it takes up damn near a 1/4 of the screen. For your convienience it has a 2d picture beside the name. In the original? 3D model WITH ACTUAL stats including armor and firepower ratings. Building in this version sends the ship into a horrible little pukepile called the queue. You shouldn't pay much attention to it because it is tucked away in the very far corner of the screen and you usually have to scroll down to see it all. To recap at this point: everything relating to researching, building, and controlling ships is rancid catpoop compared to the original. The actual 3d 'health bars' are also insanely 10x bigger in this version than the original, like they actually block the entire scene with only a handful of ships selected. Speaking of ship selection, the original let you select certain types of ships out of a larger group by giving you a text list. In this version you are given an array of icons to choose from, and lo and behold if it is the one part of the UI that doesn't fill the whole screen, but keeping with the theme of SUCKASS the icons are blurry and all look the same so at a glance you can't tell them apart. Don't fret though, if you hold the cursor over the picture FOR A FEW SECONDS the alt text pops up. The number of selected ships is also a blurry secret, shhh! In this version there are ugly unneccessary lines that show where ships are moving to or what they are targeting. Perfect for people who have never played Homeworld and have ADD or severe brain damage. Okay, there you have it, play by play every piece of the game has been a bucket of rotting fish up to this point. On to t