76561198090500482,Recommended,244160,14658411,"Posted: 25 February, 2015",all,Pontius,"When I picked up a dusty copy of Homeworld, some years after its release, and booted up this obscure 3D Space RTS, and its equally beautiful sequel, Homeworld 2, I could never have imagined that now, perhaps a Decade later,  they would once again return to my computer screen, reimagined in glorious HD.The story is powerful, at times desperate, but ultimately rewarding. The narrative is genuine, sorrowful, the voice of Fleet Command falters at the sight of the Genocide of Kharak, pilots mourn and seek revenge with rabid determination. This gives way in turn to triumpthant relief.Ships catch the light of exotic Nebulae, projectiles and lasers cast fiery arcs on their hulls. The graphical direction becomes another dimension to the story, everything is just Human enough for the gamer to be totally immersed in the struggle, the exiles clinging to hope in these ships almost becoming your own people.This re-release of Homeworld and Homeworld 2, is a fitting homage to the genius of this series. Many an hour will be lost, or invested, in joining these weary exiles on their slow, tortured, hazard filled journey to that place we all hope to find, home.10/10"
