,Not Recommended,244160,14664712,"Posted: 26 February, 2015",all,bikinihorst,"I played the original Homeworld for days on end and hoped by the infos released, it would be a remarkable bundle of glorious HD childhood remembrance. I was wrong.One of the main reasons I didn't really play and / or like Homeworld 2 was related to fleets. Yes, one of the main things elevating this game from other RTS was bothering me. Why? The AI didn't have a fixed fleet (size) like in HW1, but instead was composed of units perfectly cancelling out your whole fleet. You captured Frigates, Destroyers, Cruisers only to get them destroyed by counter-units spawned exactly for this ship.In HW1 you had a unique fleet consisting of Kadeshi, Turanic and Taiidan ships mixed with your run-off-the-mill standard units. It was simply put beautiful. They kept their original paint job and most of them performed extraordinarily. You cared deeply for your units because you couldn't build new ones to replace them, because they were unique. If you built units, it was mostly supporters and / or special ships. Why? Because resources were scarce and had to be consolidated around the necessities. You used what you had carefully and many a time you had to reload a game because you lost one too many ship or one dear to you.Then, in HW2, you had this urge to capture cool Vaygr craft like missile frigates. Boy was I proud to finally have captured a few of those. Then I harvested resources the old fashioned way and prepared a fleet to be able to counter everything I thought could be thrown at me. In the next mission I was always surprised to find the enemy being able to kill every last one of my ships at will, because his fleet strength was measured exactly by mine. This made me realize that capturing and keeping special or even more useful ships than mine was futile. I had to scrap every single one of them just to not be overrun and lose them in the next mission. After one or two missions I came to the conclusion that I had to scrap all ships excluding ship production vessels if i didn't want a mass extinction to happen. My fleet at the end and start of each mission basically was a Chinese sweat shop.This moved me farther and farther away from caring just the tiniest bit for my fleet - because why would I? Everything was interchangeable or could be rebuilt. It was always the same. Scrap and rebuild. Scrap and rebuild. At some point I just produced ships to counter the enemy, not to have an effective fleet. The ones built faster were in higher numbers than the rest, because who gives a♥♥♥♥♥♥ right? They will be scrapped either way. I realized that this was not the type of game I was expecting a HW game to be and abandoned HW2 for good.Now they made this gorgeous looking game and based it on the same ♥♥♥♥♥♥ AI fleet mechanism that HW2 had. I feel betrayed because the previews don't talk about that and just blow sugar up its♥♥♥♥♥ They removed many functions like the support frigates' repair beam or group capture with salvettes. It's a nightmare of micro management wrapped in gorgeous HD graphics. I will NOT play the campaigns of either of them because it just pisses on my childhood memories of HW1. Too many things are wrong with the game and I will wait until they address it. The forums are aflame because of the same reasons.I even bought the CE because I was so sure it would live up to the original. At the moment it's nothing more than a HW1 mod for HW2 with better graphics. The formations are broken, the launch manager is a mess, research costs money, the ""z""-with-selection-rectangle functions are missing altogether, the AI fleets are dynamically generated based on your fleet.I liked the serenity of the old HW1. You had your objective, completed it and collected resources while getting your fleet ready for the next mission. You built ships, organized groups or just watched your harvesters do their work. The new games focus more on massive battles - which are literally pre-programmed - and watch all you built up explode and scatter just to win by  a hair.If you liked the ""Transformers"" movies, this one is for you. If you liked the original HW game, you should wait."
