,Recommended,244160,14654751,"Posted: 25 February, 2015",all,Rheis Sivvi,"By the gods, this is amazing on so many levels.Some time ago, when Homeworld was first launched, I remember people commenting about it being a Masterpiece. I doubted, so I bought the game. I remember the last time I played the campaing, it was the 14th time I did it. Then, Homeworld 2 came. I played it so many times or more, not to mention the mods. Then the games disappeared. I was hoping that someday they would pop on Steam, but I was almost giving up.Until now.I think that there is no game that I've waited more than HW Remastered. When I heard that it was Gearbox who was remastering it, I was unsure of the quality of the work. Now I can die peacefully: the masterpiece is back. Remastered.A quick tech overview:-The graphics are amazing, but incredibly faithful to the original. The new models are so close to the original ones that they can fulfill their purpose: be what our ""mind's eye"" saw when we first played it. New effects, revamped textures and lightning only add to the nearly divine aspect of the game.-The music... when I first heard the choir, I cried like a baby, Ultra high quality true to the modern-day standards. And the subtitles. If you like them, they are there with a charisma of their own.-The gameplay... I played the tutorial to see if I was rusty. I was. But the controls did not change much. The UI is clean, with a deep degree of fidelity to HW2's UI. Smart move, as some are saying.Veredict:Masterpiece.11/10, worth every cent.PS: If any of you are wondering, they did not include the original pdf files in the package. I managed to find the Historical Briefing, you can find it here:http://www.homeworldaccess.net/downloads/hw1docs/HistoricalandTechnicalBriefing.pdfUpdate - 10/27/2015They have fixed a lot of errors, and it seems they're still working on it. Formations will not work as they did in HW1, but that's because the games were created based on the HW2 engine (which do not have the same formations). It is true that they add a deeper layer of strategy to the game, but their absence is not catastrophic, but rather a matter of re-learning the game.Still recommended."
