,Not Recommended,244160,14654089,"Posted: 25 February, 2015",all,Mithaldu,"In the current state i can only recommend against buying this game.It very much feels like a (very pretty) beta that has enough technical issues to feel nearly as bad as the original.If Gearbox manages to actually improve things i will amend this.As it is, have a small list of problems discovered in the first 10 minutes of gameplay: The mouse has lag (even at 160 fps), there's some form of mouse acceleration at work (most noticable when scrolling to zoom in, but not when zooming out) and there's not even a sensitivity slider, with the default being very low. (Fairly important for things like rotating the camera.) Panning to the left is nearly impossible on a multi-monitor setup since the mouse is not captured in the game window. The hud on a 1920x1200 screen is small, but can be increased in size by factors 2, 3, 4. However even a factor of 2 is already too much, since every element is literally doubled in height and width.Multiplayer is currently in beta, and makes the same mistake that killed multiplayer for the original: It forces usage of a centralized third-party service which may die at any time. There is an option for LAN multiplayer, but that is unlikely to work well on the internet.As a postscript: Since the original version is included, it's recommended to simply play that. It also has a tiny UI, but a very sharply-designed one, and the screen is locked to 4:3, but otherwise it does not exhibit the beta-like issues of the remaster."
