,Recommended,244160,16396309,"Posted: 14 June, 2015",all,LenabotSE,"Homeworld is, hands down, one of the best RTS games of all time. Not only are the gameplay mechanics amazing, but it possesses one of the best narratives in the genre. The story is emotional and moving -- but without the forced melodrama you'd find in some other games. It's a straightforward tale told with sincerity.The classic version of both games play like the original release, so check them out for the original experience.The Remastered Editions enhance the graphics... but they also rebalance gameplay mechanics. This is most apparent in Homeworld 1. Strike craft are rendered all but useless, forcing you to use corvettes as your ""fighter wings."" You also no longer have to refuel them. Frigates and capital ships have been variously nerfed or overpowered. So, if you're a veteran of the series, your ""old school"" tactics may no longer work. These changes angered some people, though I actually appreciated having a new twist on an old classic. It made the gameplay feel fresh, even though I've beaten the original version a dozen times.So, whether you're a new player or a veteran returning home, there's something for everybody. Want the original experience? Play the classic editions. Want a new twist? Play the remastered editions. Either way, Homeworld is still one of the best strategy games ever produced."
