76561197972372009,Recommended,244160,20105061,"Posted: 29 December, 2015",all,Gizmo,"Beautiful update of one of the best RTS games I've ever played. Unfortunately, under the hood lie some significant issues. In the original version of HW 1 it didn't rely on random number generation for weapons to hit their targets(and how much damage dealt), if your round visibly hit the enemy it did the appropriate damage. This means the pathfinding and formation AI were critical, especially for your smaller craft. The update didn't get this right and makes half to a third of your combat units useless. (Case in point, 20 bombers could wreck a group of 8 capital ships. I just had 70 shredded without knocking out a single one). Additionally, the resource collectors need to get reassigned repeatedly if you want to pick up everything in a map, and salvage/repair vessels used to be smart enough to figure out what needed to be done if you selected an area, but now you need to micromanage them, adding tedium. I love this game, art direction, soundtrack, story, etc with all my heart and it hurts to see part of what made the original a revelation in the genre not work properly. Pick it up and demand the developers update until it's the game it should be."
