76561198090382657,Recommended,244160,15282544,"Posted: 9 April, 2015",all,Boskov01,"I grew up with the original Homeworld back in 1999 (I was 9 then) and I remembered playing the crap out of Homeworld back then. Homeworld 2, when it came out in 2003 was meh. Shinier but too difficult and had several gameplay mechanics I didn't like.The Remaster is essentially Homeworld 1 & 2 in the Homeworld 2 engine only shiner. There is the combined multiplayer which is probably what you want since you can play as Kushan, Taiidan, Hiigaran, and Vagyr all on the same map. I don't recommend the HW1R Campaign since, even though it's in the HW2 engine, there are some gameplay mechanics that don't transition properly. For instance HW2 had a dynamic difficulty system where the difficulty of the AI in the Campaign was determined by how many ships you had at the end of the previous mission (i.e. went into hyperspace with). So having a fully functional fleet at the beginning of a mission was not in your best interests unless you wanted to get swarmed by the AI. This mechanic was transferred over to the HW1R Campaign.In HW1 Classic it's advisable that you have 6 salvage corvettes built and ready to go before the end of mission 2 to make capturing the three assault frigates in mission 3 easier (and for getting you two free Assault frigates...the third is always retired and converted into RUs) as well as shortening the amount of time it takes to salvage the cryo trays. HW1R screws that strategy up by adding additional Assault Frigates depending on your fleet size so instead of three, you're facing six and they will ignore your fighters and corvettes in favor of obliteratig the trays which can lead to a quick mission failed screen.But fortunately they do offer HW1 & 2 in their classic form which is highly recommended. I only use the remastered form to play offline skirmishes against the AI. There are a few bugs with the Remastered version though. Salvage Corvettes/Marine Frigates/Infiltrator Frigates have to be ordered to capture each individual target instead of group targeting a group of targets. However salvage corvettes can now capture enemy fighters and corvettes much easier now. Formations are a joke since in HW1 the ships stayed in formation and fought in formation. HW2 they break formation the minute they enter combat and the sphere formation, the formation meant to be the best defensive option availible, is useless as they don't form a spherical barrier around the target they're protecting.There is some saving grace in that the modding community is very active here. Many of the popular mods from Homeworld 2 Classic that were around prior to the release of the Remastered version have been uploaded here on the Steam Workshops. Even better, you don't have to go through a complicated installation process. The Remastered Version has a built in mod launcher on the main launcher. All you have to do is subscribe to the mods you want, download them (which begins automatically upon subscribing), go to the launcher, click mods on the bottom right of the launcher screen, select the mod you want to run, click select on the mod menu and then click run. It's very easy. No having to go into the game files and put files into specific folders, no having to worry about damaging the game's basic files. It's a wonderful additon that I'm very much enjoying.I highly recommend the Star Trek Continuum Mod for HW2C. It's very well done and a Remastered release is reportedly on its way."
