76561197970688081,Recommended,244160,14706449,"Posted: 1 March, 2015",all,The Metal,"Having only played 3 hours of the game at time of writing, I can confirm that the game is essentially the same as Homeworld / Homeworld 2. This is certainly not a bad thing as I have extremely fond memories of playing both of the original games, they are of the very highest quality and there really is nothing quite like them knocking around today. The remastered editions seem to use very much the same audio and gameplay mechanics just with ""HD"" textures, particle effects, shaders and lighting effects. Whilst graphics are not the most important aspect of this game, the remaster really does make for a fantastically beautiful gaming experience. I've had one crash so far, which is fine but the game as a whole is just as fantastic as the original(s)...There have been a few tweks, most notibly to the AI and the UI and the games are probably better for it. They are still insanely tough (if you don't have the correct unit types going into a level then you are surely going to be blown to bits) but hugely enjoyable. Trying the multiplayer once I've finished both of the campaigns (again) just gives me more to look out for. Only drawback so far? No Cataclysm, but hey, you can't have everything."
