76561198008225110,Recommended,244160,14686784,"Posted: 27 February, 2015",all,Tremor,"The original Homeworld is my favorite game of all time, no joke. Look at my avatar, it's been that since day one.Specifically, the singleplayer campaign was... perfection, everything I could have wanted as a gamer. Needless to say, I have been quite looking forward to this remaster. Keep in mind this review is from the point of view of a player of the original. Though, it IS relevant to all players.I mostly like it. The multiplayer, even in beta, works well and seems to run good. It's neat, though I'm not sure if balanced, to have faction from both homeworld 1 and 2 fight each other. But lets get down to what they, in my opinion, did right.-The graphics are eye porn, straight up. So pretty, and it still all looks like Homeworld. Perfect visual overhaul. I specifically noticed how much better Homeworld 1 resource collecting and missiles looked.-The story seems to be a perfect copy, and the remastered voice-overs sound exactly the same in terms of inflection, and the music is still spot-on. The atmosphere of the game is as flawless as the origonal.-Karan S'jet. Nuff' said.Now, I have two main issues, and I'll address them seperately.1. The homeworld campaign should not require resources for research. It throws off the delicate timing of how soon you can afford to build ships, as well as just makes things more expensive. In the classic I could have a much larger force at the end of mission 2, but now I'm relegated to a few measly ships because I lose a significant portion of my resources (like 10 ships worth) to researching previously free upgrades. I understand in multiplayer, but for the campaign, it can't be that hard to edit a file and adjust research costs to zero. Seriously.2. This is... a big issue. It would appear that the AI controlling homeworld 1 strike craft is severely broken. Specifically, ships don't hold formation in combat, and homeworld 1 corvettes seem to just be unable to align themselves in such a way that they actually hit anything.Here's an example from mission 2:If you played the original, you know heavy corvettes in wall formation will WRECK. When I assign this as an escort and an enemy fighter shows up, they should all turn, in formation, and concentrate fire for tremendous effect.  In this remaster, they stop, turn themselves perpendicular to the enemy, and all fly off in random directions. this allowed every single enemy to quite simply fly by my expensive fleet of corvettes without taking a single hit.I suspect this is a result of some issues related to unifying the homeworld 1 and 2 engines, but this combined with the research issue has completely soured my experience replaying the campaign, and I no longer want to since I can tell it will be nye impossible to complete with such severe drawbacks.Also, it seems like HW1 missiles are less accurate now, not sure though.That said, I recommend this because the multiplayer and homeworld 2 campaign are flawless as far as I can tell.I hope they can patch the strike craft AI issues, though patching AI to that extent post-release may be more than one can reasonably hope for. Time will tell if this issue gets patched."
