76561197997402504,Not Recommended,244160,15052772,"Posted: 25 March, 2015",all,Aged OMO,"I played the original Homeworld, mostly multiplayer, and it was one of my first online gaming addictions.  It was awesome.  When I heard it was being updated to play on modern machines with better graphics, I was really excited.  Then, I read that the game was going to use the HW2 engine ... red flag.First, the graphics are gorgeous.If you have never played any of the Homeworld games or were a fan of HW2, the Homeworld Remastered Collection will likely be very impressive and, for those folks, I can actually recommend it.If you are like me, and played the original Homeworld game (particularly multiplayer), I think you'll be disappointed.  Many of the game play mechanics from the original Homeworld are gone.  Remember corvette wall, supported by support frigates? Not happening.  Formations don't work right.  Support frigates do some odd latching thing rather than trailing behind.Multiplayer has all 4 HW races from both games and balance is proving to be a major challenge.  Again, if you loved HW2, it'll be familiar.  If you preferred the original, you're pretty much going to have to learn a new game (and one that you most likely won't like as well).Multiplayer stabilty is improved over HW2, but still has some issues.  Gearbox has released 2 patches to date and they seem to be trying to address bugs, stability and balance issues.  They've done a lot a good stuff, but it isn't the game I knew and loved.If you're an original Homeworld vet and haven't bought the game, you might want to wait a bit and keep tabs on the Gearbox forums to see what direction the game is headed."
