76561198012938369,Recommended,244160,14669818,"Posted: 26 February, 2015",all,Hungry Horny and Loaded,"TLDR;+Great Rework of the original series.-Replacement of the HW2 cast by the original HW1 (personal opinion)In my opinion, it was the voice actors, music and sound effects design that made HW2 so atmospheric and contributed greatly to its status of masterpiece.The baffingly brilliant sound design made HW2 into more than just a game; It made it into a piece of art that stands as unique amongst other games in the genre. Changes to the sound design by no means count as ""small changes"".So, you are more familiar with the HW1 cast and like them better;So, Relic intended to keep the voice actors;Does that mean we just have to shut up and share your opinion? Nope.I like the performances of the HW2 cast TONS better. To the point that i find playing this otherwise brilliant remastering barely enjoyable.Jenniffer Dawne Graveness and Eli Gabay both have such a unique tone of voice, and gave some stellar performances to boot;I mean, just listen to this, and tell me this isn't some Anthony-Hopkins-level theatrics right there:https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9GLmboCnLQYIs it wrong to want these (argueably objectively better) performances back? I don't think so.Is it silly to complain about a bit of sound in light of this otherwise brilliant and meticulous remastering? No, i care about game audio deeply, as it can make or brake the setting and atmosphere of any game, same goes for any movie and series.Now i know it's up to gearbox to decide where to go with the audio, i regret the decision they took but i respect it, for in the end, all of this the the fruit of their hard labour.What i'd like is just for the opinions of the audiophiles like myself to be respected as legitimate, instead of being brushed aside as the ""incessant nagging of nitpicky little whiners"" that i get the vibe it's being made out to be.I suppose someone might mod it in the future, however gearbox themselves have stated it might be more difficult than presumed at first glance because of the difference in sound file formats used.Seven hells if some brilliant coder person doesn't do this i swear i'll attempt it myself, all the clumsy fidgeting and confused pebcak moments notwithstanding."
