,Recommended,244160,14952512,"Posted: 18 March, 2015",all,Bad4u80,"Homeworld Remastered is quite possibly one of the best RTS games I've ever played (this is coming from someone that has put MANY days worth of time into the starcraft series among many others). I adore this game from top to bottom, the learning cruve can be a little high if you've never played a RTS game before, but after you get around to move ships and such this game really starts to shine. The amount of time you will put into each planning units movements and the sheer amount of room you have plan your next attack or searching for resources can be outright daunting but joyful all at the same time. This game takes it's time with unit speed just flying around can take a good while to just get from one side of the map where you located to the side where the enemy fleet is located if you use large ships as your main force.Now onto the combat which to me is the bread and butter of this game besides the atomosphere. During dogfights the ships behave like you would expect but they also make for some very interesting plans in the future with the way you can come below or from above with smaller units or larger ships if you prefer and wipe out a enemy force.The story is solid and I found myself wondering how I was going to overcome certain challenges that were presented to me. I really hope they start to make more games like this in the future, This is how to make a RTS game, fun and challenging all that the same time.I highly recommend this game to anybody that is a lover of the RTS genre, please make more games like this in the future!"
