76561197972690594,Not Recommended,244160,14739787,"Posted: 4 March, 2015",all,(UvG)Ninja Tom,"Never did I dare to dream that anyone would get a chance to remake Homeworld. Never.Words cannot describe my joy when I saw that preview on E3.It is an honor and a blessing to have the opportunity to talk about its new release, here in 2015.6/10Homeworld Remastered is gorgeous.And dumb.Wait, allow me to explain.Firstly, this is primarily based on my experience in the HW1R Campaign. For me, nothing else in this release matters. At all. I don't care about HW2, don't care about HW2R, hell I don't even care about multiplayer.Secondly, I am not going to be able to even pretend that I'm not comparing this to Homeworld, mostly because it is Homeworld: Remastered, the whole point of this game is for us to enjoy Homeworld again, so, if your stance is that this game should be measured in a void, and not held up to the Homeworld of yesteryear, then this review is not for you.This game is riddled with bugs. The first mission crashed to desktop, the second mission didn't register a salvage corvette going to the beacon (made me send a probe), and the third mission...The third mission.The third mission requires you to salvage 6 objects. The programmers clearly expected you to only get 5, and when this game was released in 1999, if you got all 6 then the mission wouldn't complete. Here in 2015, far in the distant future, what should I encounter but THE EXACT SAME BUG OMFG.I wouldn't have minded the scattering of new bugs, if they also hadn't brought back the exact same bugs from 15 years ago. I don't even understand how that's possible, you can't exactly copy and paste code from that long ago, it doesn't work, hell I don't even think they're in the same language, but I digress. The game has bugs, maybe its just new release issues, God, I hope so.Then we move on to the AI. When this game was first released in 1999 the AI was good for the time, but still dumb, which all games then were, for example, when telling a group of support frigates to repair a bunch of ships, they'd all bunch up on one ship and repair that, ignoring any other damaged ships until the first one was fixed, even if the other ships were taking fire and about to be destroyed. Dumb, but acceptable in those heady days.How does the modern support frigate work you ask? Simple, when you tell them to repair a group of ships, they do the exact same thing. Only NOW rather than faithfully following the fleet around, and repairing any new damage (in the same, slightly derpy way), they repair whatever damage was there when the initial command was issued, and then will float idly in space wherever they are until a new order is issued, what did they Unionize or something?Fighters and corvettes no longer stay in formation. Corvettes now make swooping strike passes like fighters instead of maintaining their orientation on foes and engaging them continuously. The new build menu's queue system is unintuitive. The launch menu now requires you to INDIVIDUALLY SELECT SHIPS TO LAUNCH. In a game where you can have up to 72 fighters. Pick them one by one. Or launch everything. And you can't shift select groups either, hell they aren't even organized, just listed in the order that they docked, which can be awkward when you want to launch fighters but all your resource collecters are docked as well.Oh right, resource collection. In a game where it can take HOURS to mine out an area (I'm dead serious) a bit of time dilation would have been just perfect, but no. You used to be able to tell a Resource Controller to guard your harvesters, and it would smartly place itself equidistant from all of them. No longer. Now it follows ONE around, which significantly increases the already incredibly long harvest times, and that's assuming the resource collectors actually return to the controller in the first place.You can't pick between the Taidan and the Kushan or change your ships coloration like you used to be able to.There is a hard limit of 14 salvage corvettes. The dynamic difficulty veers drunkenly between insane difficulty and laughable ease. Controlling vertical movement is clunky and hard to manage. Assigning orders using the shift click menu is incredibly finicky, as the menu has this odd tendency to ♥♥♥♥ING CLOSE when you are trying to select something. Oh and now you have to individually select targets for salvage corvettes instead of band box selecting.The voice acting, audio, and story are all magnificent, just magnificent, but since its the same as the original homeworld audio, voice acting and story you don't get any credit there, though I guess I should be glad you didn't manage to ♥♥♥♥ that up too.Conrad Hilton was a business savvy man who built a hotel empire from nothing.Homeworld Remastered is his great great great grand-daughter Paris.Pretty. Empty. Dumb, and riding on the success of her forefathers."
