76561197997031982,Recommended,244160,14740817,"Posted: 4 March, 2015",all,StinkySourdoughSalad,"This is the first review I've written and I must admit I feel mixed emotions about this game. I am a huge fan of Relic's work everything from the first Dawn of War to Company of Heroes. They are top shelf talent for RTS games. A remaster by Gearbox sounds like a no-brainer, however there is poor balancing for the campaign missions, it may be a throwback to earlier era of brutal difficulty but the asteroid mission in particular stands out due to poor responsiveness in simply selecting the targets. It also does not scale the difficulty for the fleet size. The sound design and visual spectacle is transcendant. This is also well-optimized and no doubt the prettiest RTS I think I have ever played mixing a celestial scale with strong artistic flair. It looks bold and unique, but given the frustration I have felt with its design and interface I am worried I will get burnt out before I am able to finish the campaign."
