,Not Recommended,244160,19832389,"Posted: 21 December, 2015",all,hougster,"A great, classic game, modernized. Some bugs, but you can work around them. Think of this as Starcraft on steroids. Models are completely redone for the remastered HW1 version, not just a slap of new skin.APRIL 26, 2016But, the bugs are huge, and the developers are apparently not wanting to make this game stable. Some annoying, game breaking bugs are:1. Collectors stop collecting randomly, you must keep an eye on them. This flaw really hurts in game when you're low on resources, much to my surprise it's because the collectors are taking a smoke break.2. You can't Kamikaze, I think only the HW2 ships can.3. You can only select one ship at a time to salvage, not a group. Apparently, salavage corvettes have a limited attention span now?4. Some ships ignore orders. Most notoriously, support frigates.5. Ships get anxious around asteroids, spaz out for awhile before moving/following an order.6. AI in CPU vs Player mode knows where you are at all times, will hyperjump to you within a minute when you try escaping. And of course, BattleCruisers always have the GravWell enabled when they jump.7. Capital ships have a limited attention span, will attack other ships despite you telling them to attack a different one in front of them.8. You cannot enable Fuel mode in multiplayer (HW1). This makes strategy less interesting, it always made those long distance attack runs a nail biting adventure.9. Not a fan of HW2, stopped 1/3 the way through.10. If the AI in multiplayer has HW2 ships, you're essentially toast. Maybe it's a different type of strategy, but I could never seem to match their fleet strength playing as a HW2 race."
