,Not Recommended,244160,21162801,"Posted: 12 February, 2016",all,Conclude,"I am writing this review only from what I've played in the original HW remaster, as that's the only reason I bought the game. This version of this game is ok. I only recommend it if you are a diehard Homeworld fan and want to see the ships in HD awesomeness. Other than that, it is actually a huge let down.The main point of this review is to list a few things that are different(in a bad way) between this and the original Homeworld.-Strike craft no longer have finite fuel and do not require refuels-Resource collectors must be constantly told to harvest, as they will stall and idle if not near any resources-You cannot capture assault frigates and use them in your fleet in the third mission. They are converted to RU's instead.-Sphere formation when guarding is laughable. Your ships form a small sphere to the side of your guarded ship, rather than encircling the ship as a sphere with the guarded ship the origin.-Strike Craft will downright LEAVE a ship they are guarding leaving it open for other craft-There are many MANY small bugs throughout what I've played so far that are just downright silly. Two examples of this, are in the second mission, it is possible that if your first salvage corvette is destroyed after salving the wreckage, any corvette afterwards will be unable to salvage. Additionally, salvage corvettes get really glitchy when capturing big ships, and when you have distraction fighters dropping like flies, time is of the essence, but when the salvage corvettes are glitching out and wasting time, it ruins a nicely executed plan.-Many ships have had their attributes changed. The Assault Frigate (not the best frigate, but still) now is much weaker than the original Homeworld.Fortunately, this release comes with the original version of Homeworld. But this game suffers from a lack of passionate programmers ensuring the underlying code works properly and is faithful to the original gameplay. It really feels like this game was outsourced by Gearbox, similar to Aliens: Colonial Marines.I'm starting to believe that if it's not Borderlands, don't buy it from Gearbox."
