76561197985160995,Recommended,244160,14954783,"Posted: 18 March, 2015",all,J-Dub,"Homeworld Remastered is a literal blast from the past. When the original Homeworld was released, there was no other game like it. You'd think combat on a 3D plane would be complicated, but through some kind of magic the people at Relic somehow perfected it. Combat is swift, heart-racing and tactical. Nothing's more satisfying than hyperspacing cloaked ships right onto an enemy, only for them to find out too late.Though, I feel combat isn't Homeworld's strongest point. It's the story. From the first cutscene, there's are waves of emotions. Fighting through the entire galaxy to reclaim your homeworld is a true struggle, and losing any ship along the way is heartwrenching.The remastered Homeworld 1 is slightly different though. Being made in the Homeworld 2 engine has removed fuel from ships and classic formations aren't quite the same. Enemy waves during the final mission (of HW1RM) have a lot of down time, either due to different damage rates, large time between waves themselves, or both. The final mission is still as epic, but I remember it being more intense in classic Homeworld 1.This collection is well worth your money. Four games for less than price of one modern game? C'mon... there's no question."
