76561197970680531,Recommended,244160,24194265,"Posted: 8 July, 2016",all,Krassimir,"Homeworld Remastered Collection is a beautiful remaster of the original Homeworld. I would recommend this game in its entirety. If you're new to the series then you will be welcomed by about 4 core faction races for multiplayer and endless hours of 3D space warfare. The only downside is the amount of multiplayer maps which are included, and the size and design of them. Currently the community doesn’t offer much in the face of new maps, which makes replayability a bit of a short ended stick. Although the 4 races are cool and somewhat unique, they lack major discernment. I would've liked a whole different race design or two in there, and sadly we don't get that with the Remastered multiplayer experience.If you like the idea of Homeworld, I would recommend this title. Also if you’re an original Homeworld fan and are looking for a replacement, this isn’t a bad choice."
