76561198065259438,Not Recommended,244160,33956572,Posted: 1 August,all,Wilhelm,"I am a huge fan of the original version, which is included with this. The only problem here is that you can't use the original mods with the Steam version, and you can't play with any of the BIG files to have a little extra fun either. You're stuck with the original, exactly as it was.The remaster is gorgeous in terms of visuals. But the UI is very broken, regardless of what certain ""professionals"" may be saying.A small example of this is that, in the original (which you can try yourself with this version), you can take 20 salvage corvettes and drag a box around several enemy capital ships, and your little fleet will try to salvage them all. It wouldn't get all of them, but it would get some of them.In the remastered version, the best you can do is send all 20 salvage ships at ONE capital ship at a time. And their armor is so weak in the remaster that most of them get picked off. That's lousy. It's easy for me to imagine that a ship with ""tug"" engines is a little harder to blow up than this.New players would probably love this game. But for the older players, it's the same story with a visual upgrade and a broken interface...don't waste your time."
